  <entry>
    <title>Does Hexo markdown escapes HTML special characters?</title>
    <link href="https://blog.yskz.dev/2023/02/01/does-hexo-markdown-escapes-html-special-characters/"/>
    <id>https://blog.yskz.dev/2023/02/01/does-hexo-markdown-escapes-html-special-characters/</id>
    <published>2023-02-01T01:46:35.000Z</published>
    <updated>2023-02-01T12:18:17.672Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In Hexo, A markdown-format post is converted to HTML.<br>HTML document needs to escape special two characters of ‘Less than’ and ‘Greater than’:<br>‘&lt;’</p><p>‘&gt;’</p><p>as:</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&amp;lt;</span><br><span class="line">&amp;gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>&lt;br&gt;<br>is written as:<br><code>\&lt;br\&gt;</code></p><h2 id="Result-of-entities"><a href="#Result-of-entities" class="headerlink" title="Result of entities:"></a>Result of entities:</h2><ul><li>&lt; and &gt; must escape manually markdown writer himself &#x2F; herself.</li><li>Other HTML entities like aportrophe(&amp;apos;) are no need to escape.</li></ul><h3 id="Escaping-special-characters-‘L-T-’-lt-‘G-T-’-gt-and-‘back-slash’"><a href="#Escaping-special-characters-‘L-T-’-lt-‘G-T-’-gt-and-‘back-slash’" class="headerlink" title="Escaping special characters ‘L.T.’(&lt;), ‘G.T.’(&gt;) and ‘back-slash’(\)"></a>Escaping special characters ‘L.T.’(&lt;), ‘G.T.’(&gt;) and ‘back-slash’(<pre lang='en'>\</pre>)</h3><p> Three special characters:<br> [ <em>less-than</em> , <em>greater-than</em> , <em>back-slash</em> ]<br>[&lt;, &gt;, \]</p><p> need a <strong>backslash</strong> is inserted in front of each of them like:<br>[\&lt;, \&gt;, \\]</p><p> not to be treated as embedding HTML tags and an <strong>escape</strong> character.</p>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;In Hexo, A markdown-format post is converted to HTML.&lt;br&gt;HTML document needs to escape special two characters of ‘Less than’ and ‘Greater</summary>
      
    
    
    
    
